==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hyperthyroidism
<hw>hyperthyroidism</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An
abnormality of the thyroid gland characterized by the pathologically
excessive production of thyroid hormones; -- also, the resulting
condition characterized by increased metabolism, weight loss, rapid
heart rate, high blood pressure, an enlarged thyroid gland and sometimes
exophthalmos. It leads to, and may be confirmed by, high plasma levels
of triiodothyronine or thyroxin.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> thyrotoxicosis.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypertrophical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hypertrophic</ent>⟦br⟧
